Great first proper day of year 2. 3 peaks, little rain, unexpected bar halfway. Scary dog, friendly hunters and mountain fresh filtered water.

Early start, sun all day. Cloud lake, another unexpected bar,  owned by nice French folk, horses on hills, first sight of snow capped mountains to foreshadow what‚Äôs to come. Sore feet. Beat George at darts in the pub.

6am. Morning moonlight shadows of two plonkers with no idea of adventures ahead . Grinding incline, terrible bocadillos, five apples, knee deep snow and a bitch of a final ascent. Wind shelters, bail out, road to France, hitchhike. Picked up by two Colombians, David and Adriana, the best people. Car got stuck in snow. We pushed. We walked more. 10pm arrive. Beer.

Woke up to rain. Follow the sounds of the river in the dark, follow the deer tracks in the snow, follow the road. Highest point of the trip, 1300m, we couldn‚Äôt see a thing! Apple Watch died halfway. Rain, wind, frozen fingers. Cute town.
